lzh_formatted:
  title: 獎諭征西都知兵馬金正純敎書
  author: 崔諴
  language: lzh
  text: 敎某。惟逆賊趙匡等。以幕鷰鼎魚之勢。且延晷刻之命。敢拒官軍。朞有餘月。師老財窮。爲害不小。伻來奏捷。實慰朕心。昔唐近臣守謙。以偏將從事於丞相裴度幕下。助平淮蔡。事載于史。以今觀之。無愧前輩。不有嘉奬。何以勸人。今賜卿金腰帶一條金花銀匣重肆拾兩緋羅夾複。全宜祗領也。故玆詔示。想宜知悉。春暄。卿比平安好。遣書指不多及。
korean:
  title: 정서도지병마 김정순을 장유하는 교서
  author: 최함
  language: kor
  text: 모(某)에게 교하노라. 역적 조광(趙匡)이 불 붙는 집에 깃들인 제비나 솥안에 든 물고기와 같은 형세이면서도 잠깐 동안이나마 목숨을 연장하려 하여, 감히 관군에 항거한 지가 일 년 하고도 몇 달이 되었다. 이에 군사는 지치고 재물은 다하여 해가 적지 않았는데 사신이 와서 승첩(勝捷)을 아뢰니, 실로 짐의 마음이 위로가 된다. 옛날 당나라 때 근신 수겸이 일개 편장(偏將)으로서 승상 배도(裴度)의 막하(幕下)에서 종사하여 배도를 도와 회채(淮蔡)를 평정해 사적이 역사에 실렸는데, 지금의 일로써 본다면 예전 사람에게 부끄러울 것이 없다. 가상히 여겨 장려함이 있지 않으면 어찌 국사에 힘쓰도록 사람들을 권장할 수 있겠는가. 이제 경에게 금허리띠 한 개와 금화은갑(金花銀匣) 무게 10냥짜리와 붉은 비단 겹옷을 주노니, 모두 공경히 받을지어다. 이에 조서를 내리는 것이니 마땅히 잘 알라. 봄날이 따뜻한데 경은 평안히 잘 지내라. 글로써 말을 다하지 못하노라.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0260_020_0150&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: An Imperial Edict of Commendation to Kim Jeong-sun, Commander of Military Affairs in the Western Garrison
  author: Choi Ham
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I hereby commend you. The rebel Zhao Kuang and his conspirators, like swallows nesting in a burning house or fish trapped in a cauldron, cling to their fleeting lives while daring to resist the imperial forces. For more than a year they have held out, yet now the army grows weary and the treasury depleted—their threat diminishes. When word came of your victory, my heart was truly gladdened.

    Once in the Tang dynasty, the courtier Shou Qian, serving as a mere subordinate general under Prime Minister Pei Du, helped suppress the rebellion in Huai-Cai, and his deeds were recorded in history. Judging by the present circumstances, your actions are no less worthy than those of the ancients. Should we not offer commendation and reward, how then can we encourage others to exert themselves in service to the realm?

    Therefore, I now grant you a golden belt, a silver ornament inlaid with gold flowers weighing forty taels, and a crimson silk brocade lined robe. Receive these gifts with proper reverence. This edict is hereby issued for your knowledge and compliance. As the spring warmth arrives, I trust you remain in good health and spirits. My words cannot convey all that I wish to say.
  footnotes:
    - 'Zhao Kuang (趙匡): A historical rebel figure whose resistance prompted this commendation of a military official''s victory.'
    - 'Shou Qian (守謙) and Pei Du (裴度): Historical Tang dynasty figures known for suppressing the Huai-Cai rebellion, invoked here as a precedent for rewarding military merit.'
    - The imagery of swallows in a burning house and fish in a cauldron conveys the desperate, doomed nature of the rebels' position.
